						<summary>

						<p>This inscription states that the temple of Añjāda-Perumāḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vēdanāthar situated on the banks of the Brahmatīrtha in the Tuṅgavaṉam (forest) in Vēlaṅgāl-paṟṟu on the east side of Āṉaimalai, together with its <hi rend="italic">tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi>, its flower gardens and its <hi rend="italic">agarams</hi> (brahmin villages) would be the place of asylum to the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭār</hi> of Kalavaḻi and the Aiñjunilai-paṟṟu. Aṉaimalai is said to be situated to the north of Tirumōgūr in Teṉpaṟappu-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
